{"type":"message","id":"00c1991a","parentId":"5f371c9b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:25:01.239Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i21qn2f7gi3q_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142433\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action for this pulse.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals document:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n2. Recent CFI Compression Experiment completed (2026-03-24)\r\n3. Key pending task: **Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)**\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"?\r\n   - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is the clear next action. The synthesis document has already identified:\r\n- CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive\r\n- Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter\r\n- NEW experiment needed: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe next step is to run the experiment described in the pending section. I should create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Computes the hybrid score for each token\r\n3. Tests the scoring against the binary thresholds\r\n4. Generates comparison results\r\n\r\nLet me check what's available:\r\n- pulse_2026-03-24 142315.md - the most recent pulse\r\n- research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md - the synthesis document\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment script to run the hybrid scoring test. This is a concrete file edit that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me write a PowerShell script to perform the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment, following the same pattern as the previous CFI experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified the \"constant format problem\" (freq=160, CFI=1.0 tokens are metaprogramming artifacts, not research signal). The pending action is to test the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) against binary thresholds.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` - document the experiment design for testing whether the hybrid scoring formula distinguishes constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens, including the test methodology and success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```markdown\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** PENDING\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nTest whether the hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes:\r\n- **Constant-format tokens** (freq≈160, CFI≈1.0) → LOW score (should be filtered)\r\n- **Research trajectory tokens** (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → HIGH score (should be kept)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula penalizes constant-format tokens because min(1, 160/120) = 1.0, BUT:\r\n- They have freq=160, which may still score high\r\n- Need to verify if CFI×freq^0.5 works better than CFI×min(1, freq/120)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Token Sets\r\n1. **Constant-format tokens** (should score LOW):\r\n   - \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n   - \"pulse\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n   - \"completed at:\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n   \r\n2. **Research trajectory tokens** (should score HIGH):\r\n   - \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96)\r\n   - \"CFI\" (freq=52, CFI=0.78)\r\n   - \"compression\" (freq=28, CFI=0.65)\r\n\r\n### Scoring Formulas to Test\r\n| Formula | Constant (160,1.0) | Trajectory (136,0.96) | Ratio |\r\n|---------|-------------------|----------------------|-------|\r\n| A: CFI × min(1,freq/120) | 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.00 | 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96 | 0.96 |\r\n| B: CFI × sqrt(freq/120) | 1.0 × 1.155 = 1.16 | 0.96 × 1.06 = 1.02 | 1.14 |\r\n| C: CFI² × sqrt(freq/120) | 1.0 × 1.155 = 1.16 | 0.93 × 1.06 = 0.98 | 1.18 |\r\n\r\n### Test: Full Pulse Corpus\r\n- **Corpus:** 200 pulses (80 train / 20 test split)\r\n- **Metric:** Precision, Recall, F1 for identifying research-relevant tokens\r\n- **Baseline:** Binary CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120) from previous experiment\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n1. Hybrid formula achieves F1 ≥ 0.7 (vs baseline 0.55)\r\n2. Constant-format tokens score in bottom 10% of all tokens\r\n3. Research trajectory tokens score in top 50% of all tokens\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nIf the hybrid formula works, we have a concrete compression objective for Layer 1 of the compression network.\r\nfile: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:24:53\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376701237}}
